        "market_mechanism": "gradient-boosted decision trees (HistGradientBoostingClassifier, max_depth=6, max_iter=200, lr=0.05) on the full 27-feature panel. Tests whether the structural break (2025-08+ regime sign inversion observed for v74/v80/v81/v83 linear models) is in the linear weight assumption rather than in the underlying alpha. Hypothesis: a tree model that captures non-linear feature interactions and adapts to local feature regimes can pass walk_forward and possibly regime_holdout where linear single-shot ranking cannot.",
        "directional_claim": "classify forward 5-day return positive vs negative on full feature panel via boosted trees; rank by predict_proba shift. Expected: walk_forward median sharpe and rank IC at least match v83 linear baseline; regime_holdout is the decisive test — if non-linear model also FAILS regime, the structural break is in the data not the model class.",
